\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces HTM vs AFS Securities Portfolio Composition Over Time. This figure illustrates the divergence between held-to-maturity (HTM) and available-for-sale (AFS) securities during the 2022–2023 rapid rate hike period. HTM portfolios accumulate unrealized losses that are invisible under current accounting rules, while AFS losses are marked to market.}}{15}{figure.caption.11}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:htm_afs}{{5}{15}{HTM vs AFS Securities Portfolio Composition Over Time. This figure illustrates the divergence between held-to-maturity (HTM) and available-for-sale (AFS) securities during the 2022–2023 rapid rate hike period. HTM portfolios accumulate unrealized losses that are invisible under current accounting rules, while AFS losses are marked to market}{figure.caption.11}{}}
